{"type":"message","id":"6616b437","parentId":"4940e3bc","timestamp":"2026-03-30T00:00:26.421Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_TfKPwVxV4DpzCN3JoHQhywB4|fc_093e06e7855dd07a0169c9bd1d04388191b883a06eebb49966","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Usage: gog calendar (cal) <command> [flags]\nBuild: v0.12.0 (c18c58c)\n\nGoogle Calendar\n\nFlags:\n  -h, --help                   Show context-sensitive help.\n      --color=\"auto\"           Color output: auto|always|never\n  -a, --account=STRING         Account email for API commands\n                               (gmail/calendar/chat/classroom/drive/docs/slides/contacts/tasks/people/sheets/forms/appscript)\n      --client=\"\"              OAuth client name (selects stored credentials +\n                               token bucket)\n      --access-token=STRING    Use provided access token directly (bypasses\n                               stored refresh tokens; token expires in ~1h)\n                               ($GOG_ACCESS_TOKEN)\n      --enable-commands=\"\"     Comma-separated list of enabled top-level\n                               commands (restricts CLI)\n  -j, --json                   Output JSON to stdout (best for scripting)\n  -p, --plain                  Output stable, parseable text to stdout (TSV;\n                               no colors)\n      --results-only           In JSON mode, emit only the primary result (drops\n                               envelope fields like nextPageToken)\n      --select=STRING          In JSON mode, select comma-separated fields\n                               (best-effort; supports dot paths). Desire path:\n                               use --fields for most commands.\n  -n, --dry-run                Do not make changes; print intended actions and\n                               exit successfully\n  -y, --force                  Skip confirmations for destructive commands\n      --no-input               Never prompt; fail instead (useful for CI)\n  -v, --verbose                Enable verbose logging\n      --version                Print version and exit\n\nCommands:\n  calendars [flags]\n    List calendars\n\n  subscribe (sub,add-calendar) <calendarId> [flags]\n    Add a calendar to your calendar list\n\n  acl (permissions,perms) <calendarId> [flags]\n    List calendar ACL\n\n  alias <command>\n    Manage calendar aliases\n\n  events (list,ls) [<calendarId>] [flags]\n    List events from a calendar or all calendars\n\n  event (get,info,show) <calendarId> <eventId>\n    Get event\n\n  create (add,new) <calendarId> [flags]\n    Create an event\n\n  update (edit,set) <calendarId> <eventId> [flags]\n    Update an event\n\n  delete (rm,del,remove) <calendarId> <eventId> [flags]\n    Delete an event\n\n  freebusy [<calendarIds>] [flags]\n    Get free/busy\n\n  respond (rsvp,reply) <calendarId> <eventId> [flags]\n    Respond to an event invitation\n\n  propose-time <calendarId> <eventId> [flags]\n    Generate URL to propose a new meeting time (browser-only feature)\n\n  colors\n    Show calendar colors\n\n  conflicts [flags]\n    Find conflicts\n\n  search (find,query) <query> [flags]\n    Search events\n\n  time [flags]\n    Show server time\n\n  users [flags]\n    List workspace users (use their email as calendar ID)\n\n  team <group-email> [flags]\n    Show events for all members of a Google Group\n\n  focus-time (focus) --from=STRING --to=STRING [<calendarId>] [flags]\n    Create a Focus Time block\n\n  out-of-office (ooo) --from=STRING --to=STRING [<calendarId>] [flags]\n    Create an Out of Office event\n\n  working-location (wl) --from=STRING --to=STRING --type=STRING [<calendarId>] [flags]\n    Set working location (home/office/custom)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":151,"aggregated":"Usage: gog calendar (cal) <command> [flags]\nBuild: v0.12.0 (c18c58c)\n\nGoogle Calendar\n\nFlags:\n  -h, --help                   Show context-sensitive help.\n      --color=\"auto\"           Color output: auto|always|never\n  -a, --account=STRING         Account email for API commands\n                               (gmail/calendar/chat/classroom/drive/docs/slides/contacts/tasks/people/sheets/forms/appscript)\n      --client=\"\"              OAuth client name (selects stored credentials +\n                               token bucket)\n      --access-token=STRING    Use provided access token directly (bypasses\n                               stored refresh tokens; token expires in ~1h)\n                               ($GOG_ACCESS_TOKEN)\n      --enable-commands=\"\"     Comma-separated list of enabled top-level\n                               commands (restricts CLI)\n  -j, --json                   Output JSON to stdout (best for scripting)\n  -p, --plain                  Output stable, parseable text to stdout (TSV;\n                               no colors)\n      --results-only           In JSON mode, emit only the primary result (drops\n                               envelope fields like nextPageToken)\n      --select=STRING          In JSON mode, select comma-separated fields\n                               (best-effort; supports dot paths). Desire path:\n                               use --fields for most commands.\n  -n, --dry-run                Do not make changes; print intended actions and\n                               exit successfully\n  -y, --force                  Skip confirmations for destructive commands\n      --no-input               Never prompt; fail instead (useful for CI)\n  -v, --verbose                Enable verbose logging\n      --version                Print version and exit\n\nCommands:\n  calendars [flags]\n    List calendars\n\n  subscribe (sub,add-calendar) <calendarId> [flags]\n    Add a calendar to your calendar list\n\n  acl (permissions,perms) <calendarId> [flags]\n    List calendar ACL\n\n  alias <command>\n    Manage calendar aliases\n\n  events (list,ls) [<calendarId>] [flags]\n    List events from a calendar or all calendars\n\n  event (get,info,show) <calendarId> <eventId>\n    Get event\n\n  create (add,new) <calendarId> [flags]\n    Create an event\n\n  update (edit,set) <calendarId> <eventId> [flags]\n    Update an event\n\n  delete (rm,del,remove) <calendarId> <eventId> [flags]\n    Delete an event\n\n  freebusy [<calendarIds>] [flags]\n    Get free/busy\n\n  respond (rsvp,reply) <calendarId> <eventId> [flags]\n    Respond to an event invitation\n\n  propose-time <calendarId> <eventId> [flags]\n    Generate URL to propose a new meeting time (browser-only feature)\n\n  colors\n    Show calendar colors\n\n  conflicts [flags]\n    Find conflicts\n\n  search (find,query) <query> [flags]\n    Search events\n\n  time [flags]\n    Show server time\n\n  users [flags]\n    List workspace users (use their email as calendar ID)\n\n  team <group-email> [flags]\n    Show events for all members of a Google Group\n\n  focus-time (focus) --from=STRING --to=STRING [<calendarId>] [flags]\n    Create a Focus Time block\n\n  out-of-office (ooo) --from=STRING --to=STRING [<calendarId>] [flags]\n    Create an Out of Office event\n\n  working-location (wl) --from=STRING --to=STRING --type=STRING [<calendarId>] [flags]\n    Set working location (home/office/custom)","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Gustavo\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774828826419}}
